From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: crackerjacques <jack@supremeoverlordjabs.co>
Date: Sat, 13 Jun 2026 12:00:00 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] phy: rockchip-inno-usb2: cancel otg/host delayed works on
 teardown

rockchip_usb2phy_otg_port_init() arms otg_sm_work during probe: the
extcon initial-state sync calls extcon_set_state_sync(), which fires
rockchip_otg_event() and schedules otg_sm_work (OTG_SCHEDULE_DELAY,
2 * HZ). The port delayed works are only cancelled in
rockchip_usb2phy_exit(), which runs when a consumer powers the PHY
down - not when probe fails or when the device is unbound.

If a later probe step returns -EPROBE_DEFER, the devm-allocated
rockchip_usb2phy (which embeds the ports and their delayed works) is
freed with otg_sm_work still queued. When the timer later expires it
dereferences the freed work and jumps through a stale function pointer:

  pc : <stale pointer into freed, reused memory>
  lr : call_timer_fn+0x3c/0x1a8
  Call trace:
   __run_timers
   run_timer_softirq
   ...
   run_ktimerd

Seen on an RK3308B (Luckfox Nova): the first usb2phy probe defers, the
retry succeeds, and the ghost timer armed by the first attempt fires
about two seconds later. It is easy to reproduce under PREEMPT_RT.

Register devm actions right after the works are initialised so they are
cancelled on the probe-error unwind and on unbind, regardless of whether
the PHY was ever powered up.

Fixes: 8dc60f8da22f ("phy: rockchip-inno-usb2: Sync initial otg state")
Signed-off-by: crackerjacques <jack@supremeoverlordjabs.co>
---
 drivers/phy/rockchip/phy-rockchip-inno-usb2.c | 27 +++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 27 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/phy/rockchip/phy-rockchip-inno-usb2.c
+++ b/drivers/phy/rockchip/phy-rockchip-inno-usb2.c
@@ -1247,6 +1247,13 @@
 	return 0;
 }

+static void rockchip_usb2phy_host_port_cancel_work(void *data)
+{
+	struct rockchip_usb2phy_port *rport = data;
+
+	cancel_delayed_work_sync(&rport->sm_work);
+}
+
 static int rockchip_usb2phy_host_port_init(struct rockchip_usb2phy *rphy,
 					   struct rockchip_usb2phy_port *rport,
 					   struct device_node *child_np)
@@ -1260,6 +1267,12 @@
 	mutex_init(&rport->mutex);
 	INIT_DELAYED_WORK(&rport->sm_work, rockchip_usb2phy_sm_work);

+	ret = devm_add_action_or_reset(rphy->dev,
+				       rockchip_usb2phy_host_port_cancel_work,
+				       rport);
+	if (ret)
+		return ret;
+
 	ret = rockchip_usb2phy_port_irq_init(rphy, rport, child_np);
 	if (ret) {
 		dev_err(rphy->dev, "failed to setup host irq\n");
@@ -1280,6 +1293,14 @@
 	return NOTIFY_DONE;
 }

+static void rockchip_usb2phy_otg_port_cancel_works(void *data)
+{
+	struct rockchip_usb2phy_port *rport = data;
+
+	cancel_delayed_work_sync(&rport->otg_sm_work);
+	cancel_delayed_work_sync(&rport->chg_work);
+}
+
 static int rockchip_usb2phy_otg_port_init(struct rockchip_usb2phy *rphy,
 					  struct rockchip_usb2phy_port *rport,
 					  struct device_node *child_np)
@@ -1311,6 +1332,12 @@
 	INIT_DELAYED_WORK(&rport->chg_work, rockchip_chg_detect_work);
 	INIT_DELAYED_WORK(&rport->otg_sm_work, rockchip_usb2phy_otg_sm_work);

+	ret = devm_add_action_or_reset(rphy->dev,
+				       rockchip_usb2phy_otg_port_cancel_works,
+				       rport);
+	if (ret)
+		goto out;
+
 	ret = rockchip_usb2phy_port_irq_init(rphy, rport, child_np);
 	if (ret) {
 		dev_err(rphy->dev, "failed to init irq for host port\n");
--
2.43.0
